description.narrative: In 2021, 580 children and women victims of violence, of whom 70% are girls aged 11 to 17, had access to the listening and protection services for children and women victims of violence. 57.53% of these cases (334 victims) who had suffered sexual violence, received medical, legal and psychosocial assistance. A manual for the management of cases of violence was validated on 28 May 2021, during a national workshop, as well as a tool for facilitating the treatment, analysis and presentation of results on cases of violence against children and women. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:10/01/2022
